{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "PlasmaClassicDecomposed",
  "description": "Plasma Classic, decomposed bit-exact through the procedural-math vocabulary. Five sinusoidal terms summed and contrast-curved:\n  v1 = sin((uv.x_a) * freq * 1.0 + t*1.3)\n  v2 = sin((uv.y_a) * freq * 0.8 + t*0.9)\n  v3 = sin((uv.x_a + uv.y_a) * freq * 0.6 + t*1.1)\n  v4 = sin(length((uv_a) * freq * 1.2) + t*0.7)\n  v5 = sin(rotated_uv.x_a * freq * 1.4 + t*1.5)\n  edge = mix(0.3, 0.02, contrast) = 0.3 - 0.28*contrast\n  out = smoothstep(-edge, edge, (v1+v2+v3+v4+v5)/5)\n\nuv_a is the legacy aspect-corrected and uv_scaled coordinate (uv.x*aspect*uv_scale, uv.y*uv_scale) centered around 0. uv_scale = 1/scale (Scale slider). freq = 3 + 5*complexity (Complexity slider). t = time * speed (Speed slider). Rotation angle for v5 is t * 0.3 (radians).\n\nOuter sliders: Complexity, Contrast, Speed, Scale — match the legacy Plasma card exactly. Pattern + Snap selectors are pending the mux'd-variant follow-up; this preset implements the Classic pattern only.",
  "presetMetadata": {
    "id": "PlasmaClassicDecomposed",
    "displayName": "Plasma Classic Decomposed",
    "category": "Diagnostic",
    "oscPrefix": "plasma_classic_decomposed",
    "available": true,
    "params": [
      {
        "id": "complexity",
        "name": "Complexity",
